<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-62-0785 </DOCNO><TEXT>Open-cycle desiccant air conditioning is described. Specific attentionis focused on a five-ton, packaged air-conditioning and heating unitdeveloped under the sponsorship of the Gas Research Institute. Featuresof the gas-fired unit include large operating cost savings, excellentfirst-cost payback, improved humidity control, high levels of fresh airventilation, and safe, reliable and quiet operation. A field evaluationof eight units is planned for a 1987 initiation.</TEXT></DOC>